The course introduces history as a field of research, its main concepts, contemporary topics and currents and given an overview of current research in Estonia. It covers different types of texts the student will tackle in their studies with main focus on evaluation, analysis and writing of academic research texts and source criticism. The course will also include tips on study skills, internship placements, studying abroad and future career prospects.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) To introduce students to specifics of historical research, methodology, new themes and currents in history. To provide an overview of research done in Estonia today.  2) To introduce different types of sources, genres and texts used in history.  3) To prepare students for writing high quality academical texts, including the choice of sources and literature, source criticism. 4) To prepare students for their further study at the institute of history and archaeology.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) Student describes different modern topics and currents in history writing.  2) Student can distinguish between popular science and academical research, and can evaluate sources critically.  3) Student finds sources and literature for her/his research projects. 4) Student writes analytical and critical academic texts that follow the guidelines of the institute.  5) Student guides her/his further studies according to her/his personal goals for further study and career prospects.
